author: Georgi Kantchev
title: Oil Prices Rise as Russia’s Action in Syria Weighs
text:
LONDON—Oil prices rose on Friday as the escalating situation in Syria added a geopolitical element to the market, long battered by an oversupply of crude.
Traders also positioned themselves ahead of a U.S. jobs report and rig-count data due later in the trading day.
